<section id="māorielectorates" class="post-section">
    <header class="post-header">
        <h2>Māori Electorates</h2>
    </header>
    <div>
        <figure class="float-left">
            <a href="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/47/New_Zealand_M%C4%81ori_electorates_%28since_2020%29.svg"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/47/New_Zealand_M%C4%81ori_electorates_%28since_2020%29.svg" alt="A map of Aotearoa New Zealand, with the 7 Māori electorates displayed on it"></a>
            <figcaption>A map of the Māori electorates<br><i>Image: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:New_Zealand_M%C4%81ori_electorates_(since_2020).svg">HTGS</a>, <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>, via Wikimedia Commons</i></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <p>There are now seven Māori electorates, which each correspond to one seat in Parliament. These are:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Hauraki-Waikato</b> – north-western North Island, including Hamilton and Papakura</li>
            <li><b>Ikaroa-Rāwhiti</b> – eastern and southern North Island, including Gisborne and Masterton</li>
            <li><b>Tāmaki Makaurau</b> – southern and central Auckland, and parts of western Auckland</li>
            <li><b>Te Tai Hauāuru</b> – western North Island, including Taranaki and Manawatū-Whanganui regions</li>
            <li><b>Te Tai Tokerau</b> – northernmost seat, including Whangārei, northern Auckland and parts of western Auckland</li>
            <li><b>Te Tai Tonga</b> – all of the South Island, Stewart Island / Rakiura, Chatham Islands, and most of Wellington</li>
            <li><b>Waiariki</b> – includes Tauranga, Whakatāne, Rotorua, Taupō</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="clear"></div>
        <p>The number of Māori registered on the Māori roll determines how many Māori electorates there are.</p>
    </div>
