<section id="māoriroll" class="post-section">
    <header class="post-header">
        <h2>Māori Roll</h2>
    </header>
    <p>Māori have the choice to either be on the Māori roll or the general roll, which determines whether your electorate vote is for the general electorate or Māori electorate you live in.</p>
    <p>Under the current legislation, Māori can choose to switch to the other roll if they want to <b>at any time</b> unless there are three months until an election (local or national). Before this legislation came about in 2023, Māori could choose when they first enrolled, then would only be able to change rolls once every five years.</p>
    <a class="cta-button" target="_blank" href="https://elections.nz/democracy-in-nz/what-is-an-electoral-roll/what-is-the-maori-electoral-option/">Read more about the Māori electoral option</a>
